      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presenting a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This naturally aspirated mill utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a broad powerband culminating in an 8,000 RPM redline. The power is managed via a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing variable M differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul, rod bearing replacement with ARP hardware, and rear subframe reinforcement to address common E46 chassis fatigue. The suspension retains its factory geometry with refreshed bushings and dampers, ensuring the telepathic steering response these cars are known for. While displaying minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-driven enthusiast vehicle, the drivetrain and structural integrity are top-tier.",
